>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>The tool &lt;code>airodump-ng&lt;/code> shares complete information regarding accessible networks including channels and BSSIDs.&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="5-capturing-handshake-data">5. Capturing Handshake Data
&lt;/h3>&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">2
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="c1"># Start capturing packets on the target network&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">sudo airodump-ng -w dump -c &lt;span class="o">[&lt;/span>channel&lt;span class="o">]&lt;/span> --bssid &lt;span class="o">[&lt;/span>BSSID&lt;span class="o">]&lt;/span> wlan0mon
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://yegormi.github.io/post/why-most-wi-fi-networks-are-insecure/img/vmware-screen-14.png"
width="3662"
height="2382"
srcset="https://yegormi.github.io/post/why-most-wi-fi-networks-are-insecure/img/vmware-screen-14_hu9276788394629509218.png 480w, https://yegormi.github.io/post/why-most-wi-fi-networks-are-insecure/img/vmware-screen-14_hu17290370422062808061.png 1024w"
loading="lazy"
alt="As indicated inside of the red rectangle - network is not empty and clients are connected and transmitting packets"
class="gallery-image"
data-flex-grow="153"
data-flex-basis="368px"
>&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Replace &lt;code>[channel]&lt;/code> and &lt;code>[BSSID]&lt;/code> with the information of your target network. The handshake occurs when any device connects to your network. Capturing this is your chance to try and test the password of the network offline.&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="6-launch-a-deauthentication-attack">6. Launch a deauthentication attack
&lt;/h3>&lt;p>Force devices to reconnect to the network, thereby increasing the probability of capturing handshake data.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Create another window of Terminal application and place it to the side of already running command done by the previous step&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">sudo aireplay-ng --deauth &lt;span class="m">0&lt;/span> -a &lt;span class="o">[&lt;/span>BSSID&lt;span class="o">]&lt;/span> wlan0mon
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>Replace &lt;code>BSSID&lt;/code> by your own. Deauthentication attacks prevent users from using the connections by making all connected devices re-authenticate so that the process can be intercepted.&lt;/p>
